cs.CR, cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.MM, cs.SE 

The paper discusses a steganographic system that utilizes network protocols such as ARP and TCP, and focuses on hidden communication in LANs. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), followed by cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The paper also involves some multimedia aspects, which could place it in cs.MM (Multimedia), and it discusses possible countermeasures, which could place it in cs.SE (Software Engineering).
